The paper deals with distributed algorithms and their time complexity, which are topics typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses lower bounds and hardness of approximation, which are topics commonly studied in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-categories.
